{
  "texts": [
    "Formally, given an original projection X 0 W 0 = Y 0 where X 0 ∈ R q×w and W 0 ∈ R w×r, the Magic Text-Encoder computes:Y 1 = (X 0 + T AG)W 0 + γ(X 0 + T AG)L 1 L 2,(11)where X 0 is the input text prompt of CLIP, Y 1 is the output of CLIP, T AG indicates newly added metamorphic tags, L 1 ∈ R w×e and L 2 ∈ R e×r are adapter parameters, W 0 are the CLIP parameters, γ is a scaling coefficient, q, w, e, and r represent the dimensions of input, intermediate, low-rank, and output, respectively.",
    "To avoid losing original capabilities, only L 1 and L 2 are updated.",
    "More details of the structure of Magic Text-Encoder can be found in the Appendix.",
    "Experimental Settings DatasetsMetamorphic video generation represents a novel paradigm, yet dedicated evaluation datasets are scarce, presenting challenges for thorough method assessment.",
    "To address this need, we utilize the ChronoMagic dataset, the first benchmark specifically designed for metamorphic video generation."
  ]
}